com.nokia.dempsy.executor
Interface DempsyExecutor

public interface DempsyExecutor

The Threading model for Dempsy needs to work in close concert with the Transport. The implementation of the DempsyExecutor should be chosen along with the Transport. If, for example, the transport can handle acknowledged delivery of messages then the Executor should be able to apply 'back pressure' but blocking in the submitLimted.

Method Detail

submit

<V> Future<V> submit(Callable<V> r)
Submit a Callable that is guaranteed to execute. Unlike submitLimted this method acts like the Callable was added to an unbounded queue and so should eventually execute.

submitLimited

<V> Future<V> submitLimited(DempsyExecutor.Rejectable<V> r)
This method queues Callables that can expire or have some maximum number allowed. Normal message processing falls into this category since 'shedding' is the standard behavior.
